CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Fish Story - When M. L. Brown tells people he caught a fish 'that long' he can prove it. He landed this 26 inch 9 1/4 pound carp at North Park Lake last Saturday.  Mr. Brown says whoppers (the fish) like this are common with him when he casts a line. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of M. L. Brown holding large fish in yard
